---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ContextAlert from '../components/ContextAlert.astro';
import Markdown from '../components/Markdown.astro';
import { cacheHeaders, randomInt } from '../utils';

export const prerender = false;

const tags = ['/revalidation', 'cats-related', 'all-pets-related'];
const headers = cacheHeaders(365, tags);

Object.entries(headers).map(([k, v]) => {
    Astro.response.headers.set(k, v);
});

const travelGuide = `
Ha Giang, located in northern Vietnam, offers a mesmerizing adventure known as the Ha Giang Loop. This scenic route winds through rugged landscapes, towering mountains, and picturesque valleys, providing an unforgettable experience for travelers seeking authenticity and natural beauty.

### Planning Your Ha Giang Loop Adventure

#### Best Time to Visit

[Ha Giang](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ha_Giang) is best explored from October to April when the weather is cool and dry, offering clear views of the breathtaking scenery.

#### Getting There

For travelers arriving from Hanoi, the journey to Ha Giang typically takes about 6-7 hours by bus or private car. [Ha Giang bus tickets](https://vexehagiang.com) can be booked online for convenience.

#### Accommodation Options

From cozy homestays in traditional Hmong villages to comfortable hotels in Ha Giang City, there are various [accommodation options](https://hagiangvisiontour.com/) to suit every traveler's preference and budget.

### Exploring the Ha Giang Loop

#### Day 1: Ha Giang City to Quan Ba

Start your journey in Ha Giang City and head towards Quan Ba, known for its twin mountains and the enchanting Quan Ba Heaven Gate.

#### Day 2: Quan Ba to Yen Minh and Dong Van

Continue through Yen Minh to Dong Van, passing by stunning landscapes and cultural landmarks such as the Dong Van Old Quarter.

#### Day 3: Dong Van to Meo Vac

Travel from Dong Van to Meo Vac, where you can visit the bustling Meo Vac Market and interact with local ethnic communities.

#### Day 4: Meo Vac to Ha Giang City

Return to Ha Giang City, taking in the final views of the majestic scenery along the way.

### Additional Tips

- **Motorbike Rental**: Explore the Ha Giang Loop at your own pace with [motorbike rental services](https://thuexehagiang.com/en/), ideal for adventurous travelers.
- **Group Tours**: Join a guided [Ha Giang Loop group tour](https://hagiangvisiontour.com) to learn about the region's history and culture from knowledgeable local guides.
- **Custom Itineraries**: Create a personalized itinerary with [Vision Travel Agent](https://visiontravelagent.com), offering tailored experiences for individuals and groups.

### Conclusion

The Ha Giang Loop promises an exhilarating adventure through some of Vietnam's most awe-inspiring landscapes. Whether you're a solo traveler seeking solitude or a group looking for cultural immersion, Ha Giang offers an experience that will leave a lasting impression.
`;

const exampleTag = tags[randomInt(0, tags.length - 1)];
---

<Layout title="Ultimate Guide to Ha Giang Loop Tour">
    <ContextAlert class="mb-4" />
    <h1 class="mb-10">Ultimate Travel Guide for Ha Giang Loop Tour</h1>
    <Markdown content={travelGuide} class="text-lg mb-10" />
    <p class="mb-8">
        Ready to embark on your Ha Giang adventure? Book your Ha Giang Loop Group Tour today!
        <a href="https://hagiangvisiontour.com" class="btn btn-lg btn-primary sm:btn-wide">Book Now</a>
    </p>
</Layout>


